race.comment: WOLF WHISTLE ZEL (1) was showing promise at the trials before finishing runner-up by a length at Ascot 2 weeks ago over 1000m. The extra furlong is ideal, and he is the one to beat for ours. FREE RIDE (4) caught the eye with a strong late finish for fifth on debut 4 weeks ago at Ascot. William Pike steps into the irons, and he can improve enough to take this out. ACE QUEEN SUITED (8) has been a beaten favourite in both of her starts to date. She cops a wide gate here, but should be suited to the step up to 1200m, and is worth another chance. Follow your money. SOVEREIGN ROCK (2) finished third against most of these at Ascot when resuming from a spell. He steps fitter, and has the talent to win a race at short notice. PAUL PARTY (3) has yet to fire in a couple of starts, but the extra 200m will help, and he can figure in the top 4 at a price.
